text:
Consider the set of all non-negative integer powers of 3.S= { 1, 3, 9, 27, 81, ... }Consider the sequence of all subsets ofSordered by the value of the sum of their elements. The question is simple: find the set at then-th position in the sequence and print it in increasing order of its elements.Each line of input contains a numbern, which is a positive integer with no more than 19 digits. The last line of input contains 0 and it should not be processed.For each line of input, output a single line displaying then-th set as described above, in the format used in the sample output.ExampleInput:1
7
14
783
1125900981634049
0Output:{ }
{ 3, 9 }
{ 1, 9, 27 }
{ 3, 9, 27, 6561, 19683 }
{ 59049, 3486784401, 205891132094649, 717897987691852588770249 }
